00:02:28.080 --> 00:02:28.830
section--

00:02:28.830 --> 00:02:32.430
is that you want to understand
how we create those fields--

00:02:32.430 --> 00:02:34.980
how we can create electric
and magnetic fields, and how

00:02:34.980 --> 00:02:37.140
that all works together.

00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:39.240
Now the first
activity, I want you

00:02:39.240 --> 00:02:43.500
to consider a cube of
length L with n electrons.

00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:47.015
There's n charges inside,
and everything is at rest.

00:02:47.015 --> 00:02:48.390
And what I want
you to figure out

00:02:48.390 --> 00:02:52.080
is what is the charge and
current density [INAUDIBLE]

00:02:52.080 --> 00:02:56.203
and j0 of this cube?

00:02:56.203 --> 00:02:57.120
There's a second step.

00:02:57.120 --> 00:03:01.330
As you can imagine, I ask you
to consider the very same thing

00:03:01.330 --> 00:03:04.750
from a moving reference frame,
S prime, with some velocity

00:03:04.750 --> 00:03:10.690
u which is the velocity of
S prime with respect to S.

00:03:10.690 --> 00:03:13.540
What is the charge in
the current density now

00:03:13.540 --> 00:03:16.150
in this new reference frame?

00:03:16.150 --> 00:03:19.570
I'd like you to figure this out.

00:03:19.570 --> 00:03:23.800
So now we look at this cube,
and the total number of charges

00:03:23.800 --> 00:03:25.390
is N. The length--

00:03:25.390 --> 00:03:28.240
or the volume is l0 cubed.

00:03:28.240 --> 00:03:32.380
And so the density is
N divided by l0 cubed.

00:03:32.380 --> 00:03:33.670
The current 0.

00:03:33.670 --> 00:03:34.630
Nothing is moving.

00:03:34.630 --> 00:03:37.930
There's no moving
charges [INAUDIBLE]..

00:03:37.930 --> 00:03:39.920
All right, this one is
more straightforward.

00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:43.450
But now in our moving reference
frame, the situation changes.

00:03:43.450 --> 00:03:47.110
Here, one of the directions--
the direction in which we are

00:03:47.110 --> 00:03:47.860
moving--

00:03:47.860 --> 00:03:49.550
is Lorentz contracted.

00:03:49.550 --> 00:03:55.300
So we have lx equal
to lx 0 or l0, times--

00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:58.060
