00:04:00.250 --> 00:04:06.490
The volume then of the same cube
in the S prime reference frame

00:04:06.490 --> 00:04:10.500
is l0 cubed divided by gamma.

00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:12.070
The number of
electrons, however,

00:04:12.070 --> 00:04:16.380
is unchanged, so the charge
density is the previous charge

00:04:16.380 --> 00:04:18.550
density divided by the volume.

00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:21.239
And if you compare--

00:04:21.239 --> 00:04:24.420
sorry, it's the charge divided
by the new volume which

00:04:24.420 --> 00:04:29.550
